      "text": "Uh and that's sort of like a second area of complication is like we call this interrupt, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "24:30",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um uh but what that means is that, you know, like Fig Jam has a bunch of node types that were made specific to Fig Jam like stickies for example.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "24:42",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Uh but because we want interrupt to feel so seamless, what this means is that if you add a new node type to a specific editor, um uh it has to work everywhere, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "24:51",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Like it would be a little bit of a bummer if you went to copy a sticky and it didn't, you know?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "24:58",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um and so this ability to like bring things between products, uh um is really cool for our users, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "25:06",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Uh but, you know, definitely adds complexity to the code.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "25:11",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 2: Gergely",
      "text": "And and as a dev like what what does this mean for for you to support stickies?",
      "tone": "Inquisitive, Clarifying"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "25:15",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 2: Gergely",
      "text": "Like I'm assuming there must be some data type somewhere of like all the things supported and then you need to figure out like how to visualize it or how to draw it or how to like how how how it maps?",
      "tone": "Inquisitive, Speculative"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "25:26",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Like how how how can we imagine? Cuz I I feel this is like interrupt is is something that most devs don't need to worry about until you do.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
