    {
      "timestamp": "28:09",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "I think that this like mass behavior concept is is like taken from how uh uh a lot of game engines run, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "28:17",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "So there's like a a priority list of mass behaviors. If one of them accepts the event, it doesn't go to to the next one, you know?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "28:26",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um so it's like our own sort of like delegation pattern that often uh the browser would handle for you, but because we're running in C++, it's all written from scratch.",
