    },
    {
      "timestamp": "32:57",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "Yeah, um I could chat a little bit about like how single slide view had some really interesting challenges.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "33:02",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 2: Gergely",
      "text": "Oh wait, love that. Cuz this is something I I I don't think most people would assume. Like it's how hard could it be?",
      "tone": "Appreciative, Intrigued"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "33:09",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 2: Gergely",
      "text": "It's it's this and actually you you said earlier, right? That oh, we knew this would be pretty simple. That's why we left it for later.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "33:17",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "Yeah, by simple, it's very relative. Yeah. Um, but yeah, like single slide views in this really interesting spot where um like collapse state, um like collapsing slides and expanding them.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Reflective"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "33:31",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "We don't want to like save that to your file at all. Um like we'd want to save stuff like the the order of slides in the grid to the file, but we don't want to save stuff like are these collapsed or not to the file.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "33:43",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "So in order to render um like this this carousel over here, we've got a bunch of state that like lives inside of web, and then a bunch of state that lives inside of the editor inside of full screen.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "33:55",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "And we got to like have a bunch of complicated code to um sort of like coales those in order to figure out like what to render here.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "34:04",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "Um on top of that, there's like a ton of crazy technical challenges to solve in terms of like dragging slides around, um and like making sure that like if I were to drag um these three slides, which like right now they're their own row in the slide grid.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "34:21",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "If I want to like drag this title this this slide out and then like move it into this row, um we got to make sure like this row is still preserved up there.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "34:32",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "Um but if I were to drag this entire row and like make it sort of a child, we got to like delete that first row and then like combine this row together.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "34:40",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "So there's a lot of like really interesting algorithm stuff to like um coales like sort of changes from the carousel um inside of web as well as like other users like dragging stuff around inside of full screen, maybe across like multiple rows or something.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "34:57",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 3: Noah",
      "text": "And like combine those two together in a way that's like that feels like safe for multiplayer.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:02",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "So yeah, I",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:05",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Yeah, yeah. This is a good thing to like, yeah.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Affirmative"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:09",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Yeah, so like this like intersection of like editing and multiplayer is like a really interesting part of the Figma stack.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Comparative"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:17",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um everything is multiplayer first. For things to be local, you have to like opt out of it being sent.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:24",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "But what's interesting about um reordering stuff in single slide view is we do um there's a bunch of operations that you can do that can move like a lot of slides at once.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:39",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um but because we wanted it to be multiplayer friendly, there's a lot of work under the scene or under behind the scene, under the hood, that's happening to like perform the the minimum number of mutations possible because the more mutations that you do, the less multiplayer friendly something is, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "35:58",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "So like you can if you're like load Yeah.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:01",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "If you're picturing the slide grid, right? And if we move the bottom row to the top, in a in a naive way, um when you do that mutation, you're changing every single slide's XY coordinate, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:17",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 2: Gergely",
      "text": "Well, that's the most obvious thing to do, right?",
      "tone": "Affirmative"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:19",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Yeah. And that's how slides worked for a a while. Um but then how we ended up solving this is our like ethos was was to do the minimum number of mutations, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:31",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Like ideally the number of mutations are the number of slides that you drag.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:37",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um and the way that we achieve this under the hood is actually using um the auto layout nodes within Figma design.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:49",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "So what I mean by that is each row is in its own node, right? We call it the slide row node.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "36:57",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "And then each of those nodes is within uh a slide grid node, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:04",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "So each each slide is now two levels deep.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:07",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um we have an existing construct called parent index, which was made for reordering stuff within frames and reordering stuff within auto layout.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:17",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "Um and what a parent index is is it's a struct that has a a reference to the parent's ID as well as uh uh an index represented as a float from zero to one.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:30",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "And so by doing it this way, if you reorder just one thing for example, you only have one mutation, right?",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:38",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "So I change something from the beginning to the end, only that thing's parent index has to change.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:44",
      "ad": false,
      "speaker": "Speaker 1: Jonathan",
      "text": "And then each client is responsible for recomputing the layout, right? Just to like move things around visually.",
      "tone": "Explanatory, Technical"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": "37:51",
      "ad": false,
